WEBVTT

00:07.229 --> 00:10.104
I've had enough!
Leaks in Red Hook, leaks in City Hall.

00:10.771 --> 00:12.830
<i>You need to find them, Buck.</i>

00:12.854 --> 00:14.146
<i>Plug them.</i>

00:16.896 --> 00:19.997
Whoever is leaking to the
City Without Fear site must be punished.

00:20.021 --> 00:22.830
<i>Find out who it is, turn them over to me.</i>

00:22.854 --> 00:24.955
<i>It's my inside guy,
only he doesn't know it.</i>

00:24.979 --> 00:27.789
If you are leaking stuff,
anything, stop.

00:27.813 --> 00:29.021
We could get hurt.

00:29.438 --> 00:32.164
<i>Vanessa killed Foggy
and nothing happened.</i>

00:32.188 --> 00:33.563
<i>A line was crossed.</i>

00:35.604 --> 00:38.164
Ever since Foggy died,
I didn't know who I was anymore.

00:38.188 --> 00:39.455
What I did,

00:39.479 --> 00:41.414
<i>what that woman had me do,</i>

00:41.438 --> 00:43.104
I had to get my mind back.

00:43.771 --> 00:45.622
<i>One good deed.</i>

00:45.646 --> 00:47.854
<i>It levels the scales again.</i>

00:53.146 --> 00:54.854
Wilson...

00:56.896 --> 00:58.813
Vanessa!

03:08.646 --> 03:10.830
I need blood pressure.
I need heart rate stat.

03:10.854 --> 03:12.330
- What's happening?
- Heart rate--

03:12.354 --> 03:13.455
- No, no, no.
- Sir, sir,

03:13.479 --> 03:15.247
- you cannot be in here right now.
- Get her!

03:15.271 --> 03:17.664
- Sir, you cannot be here.
- Vanessa. What is happening here?

03:17.688 --> 03:19.396
- Sir, sir.
- Vanessa!

03:20.396 --> 03:21.396
<i>Vanessa...</i>

03:23.604 --> 03:25.830
<i>- Sir, sir. Get back.
- Vanessa!</i>

03:25.854 --> 03:29.372
<i>Sir, sir. Mr. Mayor,
I understand that you are anxious,</i>

03:29.396 --> 03:32.289
and we will get you all the information
as soon as possible.

03:32.313 --> 03:34.580
- Can you...
- Yes, yes. Okay. Sir.

03:34.604 --> 03:36.205
- Sir, please.
- Sir, please.

03:36.229 --> 03:38.729
- Sir, please.
- Sir, let them do their job.

03:51.354 --> 03:52.580
All hands on deck.

03:52.604 --> 03:54.188
I need you to clear the schedule.

03:55.021 --> 03:57.872
- Yes! You need to...
- Like I said, absolutely no comment.

03:57.896 --> 03:59.872
How many times
do I have to tell you this, huh?

03:59.896 --> 04:01.039
I'm not gonna have to... I don't know when

04:01.063 --> 04:03.344
- a statement's gonna be ready, all right?
- Yes. Yes, go.

04:05.854 --> 04:07.063
If you have them...

04:09.646 --> 04:10.771
keep them alive.

04:11.188 --> 04:12.479
Uh, we don't, sir.

04:12.938 --> 04:13.938
Not yet.

04:14.979 --> 04:16.688
Pretty sure we have them surrounded.

04:17.688 --> 04:19.813
Sir, I want to find them as bad as you do.

04:20.063 --> 04:21.063
No.

04:22.729 --> 04:23.729
You don't.

04:24.604 --> 04:25.688
You couldn't.

04:27.146 --> 04:29.188
Whatever you need, use it.

04:29.688 --> 04:30.688
You got it, sir.

04:32.354 --> 04:33.688
Officer Powell...

04:35.271 --> 04:36.271
Alive.

04:38.938 --> 04:39.938
Yeah.

04:45.479 --> 04:46.914
The tower is ready.
Have a seat.

04:46.938 --> 04:48.563
Let's move out.
Check that side.

04:56.771 --> 04:58.205
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- Over here.

04:58.229 --> 04:59.354
- Here, here.
- Let's go.

05:07.104 --> 05:08.604
Prep towels, where are they?

05:10.938 --> 05:13.188
- Now!
- Whatever you need, man. We're with you.

05:14.563 --> 05:16.372
You don't have to do this.

05:16.396 --> 05:17.497
- Hold still.
- This is balance.

05:17.521 --> 05:19.164
- You know it.
- Shut up.

05:19.188 --> 05:23.122
<i>Check in there. Check the door!</i>

05:23.146 --> 05:25.438
- Do you have a boiler?
- Yeah, old shit back there.

05:26.479 --> 05:28.479
- Yeah, let's go.
- Leave me here.

05:28.979 --> 05:30.289
None of this matters now.

05:30.313 --> 05:31.688
It matters to me.

05:33.563 --> 05:34.872
Yeah, uh...

05:34.896 --> 05:36.313
No, no comment on that.

05:37.604 --> 05:39.896
I don't know when we're gonna have
a statement ready. No.

05:41.979 --> 05:42.979
Is she dead?

05:44.063 --> 05:46.937
What kind of sick
fucking question is that?

06:03.146 --> 06:04.539
How did you find me here?

06:04.563 --> 06:07.164
Seriously? I mean, how many hospitals
do you think there are, Daniel?

06:07.188 --> 06:09.205
- BB, you can't be here right now.
- Um...

06:09.229 --> 06:12.289
- Actually, technically, legally, I can.
- BB, think.

06:12.313 --> 06:14.104
Nobody can know where she is.
It's... It's...

06:14.979 --> 06:17.497
The mayor's not in a good place.
You gotta go.

06:17.521 --> 06:18.580
Okay.

06:18.604 --> 06:20.854
I-- I get it. I'll go, but just tell me.

06:22.021 --> 06:23.021
Is she alive?

06:24.563 --> 06:27.289
Look, there's a ton of chatter out there.
You have no idea.

06:27.313 --> 06:28.705
It's, like, crazy right now.

06:28.729 --> 06:31.021
And I just want to make sure
I get the story right.

06:33.729 --> 06:35.854
We're really fucking
doing this right now, huh?

06:41.729 --> 06:43.563
I... I'm so sorry.

06:45.146 --> 06:48.021
I shouldn't have come.
Just forget that I came, okay?

06:58.313 --> 07:00.063
She's in critical condition.

07:01.521 --> 07:03.854
They're... They're really lucky
to have you.

07:16.813 --> 07:17.813
Mr. Fisk.

07:20.396 --> 07:21.396
Mr. Fisk.

07:24.938 --> 07:26.021
Arash Merati.

07:26.854 --> 07:28.080
Happy to meet you.

07:28.104 --> 07:29.188
Dr. Merati.

07:30.188 --> 07:32.580
Please understand that
I am here to do whatever I can

07:32.604 --> 07:34.063
- for your beloved wife.
- Yeah.

07:34.563 --> 07:36.521
I had a chance to look over her chart.

07:37.313 --> 07:40.122
She is, as you know,
in quite a precarious position.

07:40.146 --> 07:41.146
Yes.

07:41.646 --> 07:43.021
I've heard that you're...

07:43.813 --> 07:45.563
the top man in your field.

07:46.354 --> 07:49.313
Well nothing is certain where the mind
meets the soul, Mr. Fisk.

07:50.063 --> 07:53.164
But that said, I will do
everything in my power for her.

07:53.188 --> 07:54.229
Thank you.

08:03.479 --> 08:06.247
<i>Knowing what a disaster
Verizon is in Chelsea,</i>

08:06.271 --> 08:10.979
I can only imagine what sort of
cellular joy awaits me in central Vermont.

08:11.938 --> 08:15.146
Hello.

08:30.438 --> 08:34.604
May I ask why you chose
not to include this piece tonight?

08:34.854 --> 08:37.414
I think it's pretty obvious
why I chose not to include it,

08:37.438 --> 08:40.979
but if you feel differently,
by all means, why should I put it up?

08:43.313 --> 08:44.313
I don't know.

08:44.563 --> 08:46.396
There's just something about it.

08:49.604 --> 08:51.164
Do you understand

08:51.188 --> 08:52.955
what keeps us in business?

08:52.979 --> 08:56.729
What pays for the cute little
gray shoes that you're wearing?

08:59.313 --> 09:00.688
But I can tell you...

09:03.479 --> 09:07.354
that if the right person
walks through that door

09:08.313 --> 09:09.979
and sees this painting...

09:11.438 --> 09:13.789
sees his own deep, inexorable,

09:13.813 --> 09:17.688
miserable emptiness
reflected right back at him...

09:18.938 --> 09:20.455
I can promise you,

09:20.479 --> 09:22.938
you can add two zeros to the list price,

09:23.688 --> 09:27.854
and it'll sell faster
than any other piece out front.

09:29.521 --> 09:31.229
The piece stays right where it is.

09:31.729 --> 09:34.354
Your call.

09:45.688 --> 09:47.039
I'm bleeding out.

09:47.063 --> 09:48.747
I've seen it enough times to know.

09:48.771 --> 09:50.521
I'm not interested
in your opinion.

09:51.729 --> 09:52.979
I've earned this...

09:54.021 --> 09:56.396
many times over. It's okay.

10:03.938 --> 10:05.188
You think she's dead?

10:07.229 --> 10:08.229
I don't know.

10:09.813 --> 10:10.813
Come on.

10:12.104 --> 10:14.188
And if she is, it all balances.

10:15.771 --> 10:17.688
Your friend, Fisk's wife.

10:18.771 --> 10:21.313
Scales settled.

10:22.354 --> 10:24.854
- And I'm ready for judgment.
- Oh, good for you.

10:25.938 --> 10:27.188
You're not listening.

10:29.271 --> 10:32.521
That night you threw me off the roof,
I was supposed to die.

10:33.021 --> 10:35.271
Four-story. No one survives that.

10:35.938 --> 10:36.938
And yet...

10:37.771 --> 10:39.438
Maybe that's the grand design.

10:41.229 --> 10:42.229
You're getting it.

10:43.438 --> 10:44.646
No, I'm not getting it.

10:46.021 --> 10:48.104
If she's dead. Vanessa.

10:49.229 --> 10:50.372
That's just murder.

10:50.396 --> 10:52.062
Vanessa, Foggy--

10:58.479 --> 10:59.521
Don't say his name.

11:01.813 --> 11:04.104
You don't get to say his name.
Do you understand?

11:05.563 --> 11:09.289
- You--
- Tell me you understand.

11:09.313 --> 11:10.438
Don't say his name.

11:13.729 --> 11:16.289
<i>Even the best avocados
have to do grunt work.</i>

11:16.313 --> 11:18.747
<i>I guess we're gonna have to
break it to Josie that we're not</i>

11:18.771 --> 11:21.229
- paying off the tab tonight.
- She'll understand.

11:21.688 --> 11:25.372
Lionel McCoy, 29 years old,
possession of multiple narcotics,

11:25.396 --> 11:27.247
including, but not limited to,

11:27.271 --> 11:29.497
Oxy, Moxy, Roxy,

11:29.521 --> 11:31.247
and wait for it, Xoxy.

11:31.271 --> 11:33.330
Christ,
guy's a walking pharmacy.

11:33.354 --> 11:36.289
Throw in a firearms charge, fake ID,

11:36.313 --> 11:38.604
intent to distribute,
obstruction of justice.

11:39.604 --> 11:41.955
Some yada. A little more yada
and yet another yada.

11:41.979 --> 11:43.664
And this guy is looking down the barrel--

11:43.688 --> 11:45.604
Wait, wait, wait. Okay, hold on.
Let me guess.

11:46.313 --> 11:48.521
I want to say 12 to 15.

11:49.271 --> 11:50.539
I'm sorry, Mr. Murdock.

11:50.563 --> 11:52.955
- The answer is actually 10 to 12.
- Oh, come on.

11:52.979 --> 11:54.914
- I was so close.
- But thank you for playing with us.

11:54.938 --> 11:56.664
And we do hope you enjoyed your stay

11:56.688 --> 11:59.289
in the correctional facility.

11:59.313 --> 12:01.330
Okay, what do you say?
Uh, we ask for six to eight,

12:01.354 --> 12:02.955
he's out in five for good behavior.

12:02.979 --> 12:06.914
Yep. Levine wants him to plead out,
so we take the best offer on the table.

12:06.938 --> 12:09.830
Under no circumstances
does this go to trial.

12:09.854 --> 12:10.914
Heard.

12:10.938 --> 12:12.039
After you, Counselor.

12:12.063 --> 12:13.604
Why, thank you, Counselor.

12:17.729 --> 12:20.830
Good afternoon, Mr. McCoy.
My name is Matthew Murdock.

12:20.854 --> 12:22.854
- This is my associate--
- Foggy the Fembot?

12:25.104 --> 12:26.372
Ray?

12:26.396 --> 12:28.330
You-- You know each other?

12:28.354 --> 12:30.705
Guy upstairs got a sick
sense of humor, don't he?

12:30.729 --> 12:32.188
We, um...

12:33.854 --> 12:35.729
grew up in the same building.

12:36.729 --> 12:38.164
Isn't your name Ray?

12:38.188 --> 12:40.938
What, you think I'd go by Lionel
in that neighborhood?

12:41.479 --> 12:43.813
You know, Fembot,
he used to clean my sneakers.

12:44.854 --> 12:46.622
- Didn't you?
- Maybe we could refrain

12:46.646 --> 12:48.122
from the name-calling, Mr. McCoy?

12:48.146 --> 12:50.205
- What's with him? You blind or something?
- How--

12:50.229 --> 12:52.247
How's, um, Connor?

12:52.271 --> 12:54.104
He moved upstate last year.

12:54.771 --> 12:55.979
Oneonta.

12:56.646 --> 12:58.955
I don't know.
Last I heard he was doing roofs.

12:58.979 --> 13:01.271
Some shit like that.
Gutters, maybe. I don't know.

13:01.688 --> 13:03.479
Knocked up the first chick he could.

13:04.521 --> 13:06.372
Okay, maybe we should, uh...

13:06.396 --> 13:08.188
Oh, yeah, please.

13:09.354 --> 13:12.664
We, uh, used to... hang out.

13:12.688 --> 13:14.580
Me and his brother, I mean.

13:14.604 --> 13:15.872
We were best friends.

13:15.896 --> 13:18.313
- The aforementioned Connor.
- Mmm-hmm.

13:18.729 --> 13:21.247
All right, uh, Mr. McCoy,
you're facing a laundry list

13:21.271 --> 13:22.747
- of state charges. I suggest--
- It's all bullshit.

13:22.771 --> 13:24.830
Regardless,
our firm was retained to represent you,

13:24.854 --> 13:27.146
and Mr. Nelson and I would like--

13:28.063 --> 13:29.063
You Mr. Nelson?

13:29.854 --> 13:31.813
- Is that supposed to be you?
- Foggy?

13:32.646 --> 13:35.289
You wanna tell your friend here what
the firm's professional advice would be?

13:35.313 --> 13:37.313
Yeah, yeah. Go ahead, Mr. Nelson.

13:38.063 --> 13:39.063
What do you got?

13:40.229 --> 13:42.854
Right. Well, we, um...

13:44.521 --> 13:46.747
Given the charges,
the evidence against you,

13:46.771 --> 13:49.563
we suggest that you take a plea deal.

13:51.188 --> 13:53.414
We ask for a reduction in sentencing.

13:53.438 --> 13:55.479
And best case scenario, you're out in...

13:56.021 --> 13:59.080
- five to six.
- Or three to four with exemplary behavior.

13:59.104 --> 14:01.080
- Oh, five to six.
- Three to four if you...

14:01.104 --> 14:02.789
If, if, if, if, if I what?

14:02.813 --> 14:04.438
If I-- If I find God?

14:05.354 --> 14:07.789
Huh? If I-- If I mop the john?
Wait the library?

14:07.813 --> 14:09.914
I believe they call it rehabilitation,
Mr. McCoy.

14:09.938 --> 14:11.188
Mmm-hmm. You don't understand.

14:11.771 --> 14:14.021
The guys I work with want me dead.

14:15.021 --> 14:17.914
I mean, that's the whole reason
you two are even here in the first place.

14:17.938 --> 14:19.039
Cop a deal,

14:19.063 --> 14:20.354
they told you, right?

14:21.104 --> 14:23.813
No trial. Huh?

14:24.521 --> 14:25.646
You want to know why?

14:26.396 --> 14:30.789
Because they got about ten guys
on the inside just waiting to take me out.

14:30.813 --> 14:32.330
All right? That's how this ends.

14:32.354 --> 14:34.914
That's how this goes.
All right? So, it's not three to four,

14:34.938 --> 14:37.289
it's not six to eight
if I'm a little good boy. All right?

14:37.313 --> 14:39.688
It's 24 hours, counselor.

14:40.271 --> 14:42.688
I'm a dead man the second I go in.

14:43.396 --> 14:44.438
So...

14:46.271 --> 14:47.729
I'm not signing shit.

14:49.188 --> 14:51.205
I'll take my chances
with a public defender.

14:51.229 --> 14:53.289
All right. Take it easy.
Back-- Back up here.

14:53.313 --> 14:55.563
What-- What are you talking about?

14:57.146 --> 14:59.479
You two don't even know
who you work for, do you?

15:10.729 --> 15:11.854
This is Wesley.

15:14.479 --> 15:15.479
Right.

15:17.271 --> 15:18.271
I'll let you know.

15:22.563 --> 15:25.063
We may have an issue with the Lion.

15:30.021 --> 15:31.813
Are you familiar with Bitcoin?

15:33.896 --> 15:35.313
In light of the Russians...

15:38.271 --> 15:40.396
we should start diversifying.

15:42.354 --> 15:44.479
In this new world...

15:46.854 --> 15:50.979
we can no longer be old-fashioned
in our way of thinking.

15:52.271 --> 15:54.830
I do have some contacts
in the crypto space,

15:54.854 --> 15:56.622
but if I may, I would suggest

15:56.646 --> 15:59.688
it might be too volatile

16:00.271 --> 16:01.372
for our needs, sir.

16:01.396 --> 16:05.521
Hmm. Now, perhaps you have other ideas.

16:06.771 --> 16:08.063
Come to think of it,

16:08.354 --> 16:11.854
I have a friend who runs an art gallery.

16:13.438 --> 16:16.354
Blue chip. Real money.

16:17.563 --> 16:19.646
It could be an interesting market for us.

16:21.646 --> 16:22.854
The art world.

16:23.813 --> 16:24.854
Pretension.

16:26.188 --> 16:30.021
And airs of posing as something...

16:31.521 --> 16:32.854
meaningful.

16:59.271 --> 17:00.372
<i>Keep moving.</i>

17:00.396 --> 17:01.604
<i>We need to get you help.</i>

17:02.521 --> 17:04.705
No, no, no. No!

17:04.729 --> 17:06.205
No, no! Come on.

17:06.229 --> 17:07.872
Stop it.

17:07.896 --> 17:10.813
Stop!

17:11.604 --> 17:14.705
This is pointless.

17:14.729 --> 17:16.063
Let's be real.

17:16.688 --> 17:18.229
You're not gonna mourn me.

17:19.354 --> 17:20.354
Go on, get up.

17:21.521 --> 17:23.872
- You need help. Let's go.
- Mmm-mmm.

17:23.896 --> 17:26.330
- Come on.
- Get your fucking hands off me!

17:26.354 --> 17:29.021
Come on!

17:32.563 --> 17:34.396
First, you try to kill me,

17:34.938 --> 17:36.813
and then you try to save me,

17:38.063 --> 17:41.563
and I'm the one who needs help?

17:44.479 --> 17:47.104
I'm trying to save you
because I tried to kill you.

17:48.771 --> 17:50.563
I lost sight of that on Josie's roof.

17:52.646 --> 17:54.604
Maybe tonight's penance is mutual.

17:57.146 --> 17:58.146
Come on.

17:58.854 --> 18:01.521
Come on.

18:08.896 --> 18:09.997
You said Henderson?

18:10.021 --> 18:11.688
- Hernandez.
- Oh, damn.

18:13.813 --> 18:16.330
All right. Punching out
before the elevator rush.

18:16.354 --> 18:17.521
Have you got plans?

18:18.854 --> 18:19.914
Allowance?

18:19.938 --> 18:21.021
Oh, that's right.

18:21.979 --> 18:23.604
What are we, uh... What are we up to?

18:24.729 --> 18:27.955
Seventeen-hundred even as of tonight.

18:27.979 --> 18:31.122
What do you think?
Eighteen more months

18:31.146 --> 18:33.414
before we open doors
on Murdock and Nelson?

18:33.438 --> 18:35.021
Congratulations, fuckos.

18:35.688 --> 18:37.372
Great job at the precinct today.

18:37.396 --> 18:39.289
All you had to do
was have the guy sign his name.

18:39.313 --> 18:40.789
Didn't even have to be legible.

18:40.813 --> 18:42.896
Plead out, sign the papers, move on.

18:43.604 --> 18:45.122
- But, no.
- Jeff, we...

18:45.146 --> 18:47.438
I'm sorry. Did you mean "Mr. Levine"?

18:48.229 --> 18:50.330
Right, yes. Sorry.

18:50.354 --> 18:51.938
- Mr. Levine, we--
- Guess what?

18:52.354 --> 18:53.354
I don't care.

18:53.979 --> 18:55.899
It's the public defender's problem now,
isn't it?

18:56.646 --> 18:58.872
Unfortunately, they need all these papers,

18:58.896 --> 19:01.479
collated and delivered to their office
by Monday morning.

19:02.479 --> 19:04.021
Happy Fraturday, fucknuts.

19:06.354 --> 19:07.437
Have a nice weekend.

19:10.271 --> 19:12.039
He's definitely into
something weird.

19:12.063 --> 19:13.896
Totally. Like feet.

19:14.729 --> 19:16.063
What's wrong with feet?

19:16.438 --> 19:18.122
Nothing. I'm just saying that

19:18.146 --> 19:19.497
I can imagine Mr. Levine

19:19.521 --> 19:21.830
doing some weird shit with feet.
That's all.

19:21.854 --> 19:22.854
Gross.

19:25.063 --> 19:26.705
Exhibit C, column two.

19:26.729 --> 19:28.313
Column two, exhibit C.

19:30.021 --> 19:31.354
Just, uh, for the record,

19:31.813 --> 19:33.789
I don't have a problem with feet.

19:33.813 --> 19:35.770
You're also not not weird, so...

19:38.604 --> 19:39.604
Whoa.

19:40.938 --> 19:41.938
What?

19:42.271 --> 19:43.330
The warrant.

19:43.354 --> 19:47.021
The address on the warrant they used
to access his apartment, it's wrong.

19:47.563 --> 19:50.979
It says 536 West 49th Street,
apartment 5E.

19:51.604 --> 19:52.705
That isn't correct?

19:52.729 --> 19:54.354
It's 536 1/2.

19:54.729 --> 19:57.289
That's where he lived.
The McCoys, I mean, that was our address.

19:57.313 --> 19:59.479
536 1/2 West 49th.

20:01.104 --> 20:02.580
No, that-- That can't be right.

20:02.604 --> 20:03.854
It is right.

20:04.938 --> 20:06.979
I mean, it's a clerical error, but...

20:08.646 --> 20:09.771
this is invalid.

20:10.771 --> 20:14.372
Everything discovered in this warrant
is fruit of the poison tree.

20:14.396 --> 20:15.396
It's inadmissible.

20:16.938 --> 20:19.063
Which means that piece of paper is...

20:19.688 --> 20:21.354
Get-out-of-jail free card.

20:25.771 --> 20:26.771
What do we do?

20:30.354 --> 20:32.914
Oh, come on, Foggy.
It's not like he deserves to walk.

20:32.938 --> 20:35.080
I don't recall the word "deserve"

20:35.104 --> 20:36.396
coming up in law school.

20:36.729 --> 20:38.789
He's in bed with the mob,
he's selling drugs,

20:38.813 --> 20:40.414
he's poisoning the neighborhood.

20:40.438 --> 20:41.771
Yeah, but...

20:42.271 --> 20:45.372
But what? He was also a raging prick
to you when you were kids?

20:45.396 --> 20:48.205
You want to spring the guy
who calls you Foggy the Fembot?

20:48.229 --> 20:50.313
No, I don't.

20:51.313 --> 20:52.313
But, Matt...

20:52.771 --> 20:54.122
we are his attorneys.

20:54.146 --> 20:56.622
- We're associates.
- Don't get technical.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.872
- Either way, Jeff made it sound like--
- Mr. Levine.

20:58.896 --> 21:00.497
- Thank you.
- Okay, okay, fine.

21:00.521 --> 21:03.289
Dark Lord of Unspoken Kink Levine

21:03.313 --> 21:05.497
made it sound like
we're not only off the case,

21:05.521 --> 21:07.479
but our badges might not work on Monday.

21:08.354 --> 21:09.688
Ray, Lionel...

21:10.146 --> 21:11.705
he had a hard life, Matt.

21:11.729 --> 21:13.539
Aw! Cue the violin.

21:13.563 --> 21:16.247
His dad, he was not a good guy.

21:16.271 --> 21:18.039
And their mom, Suzanne, she drank.

21:18.063 --> 21:20.705
A lot. She died when we were
in the eighth grade.

21:20.729 --> 21:21.789
Okay?

21:21.813 --> 21:24.021
Cirrhosis, liver failure.

21:24.229 --> 21:26.372
He never had a chance.

21:26.396 --> 21:28.747
His brother did though, didn't he?
What was his name? Connor?

21:28.771 --> 21:30.354
Connor was younger.

21:30.604 --> 21:32.205
Lionel took the brunt of it.

21:32.229 --> 21:34.914
- I didn't like him.
- And you want to let him out

21:34.938 --> 21:37.938
to continue to do horrendous things
to a whole bunch of new people.

21:38.688 --> 21:41.080
- I want to do the right thing.
- I don't know, Foggy.

21:41.104 --> 21:42.104
I don't know.

21:43.479 --> 21:46.122
You sell drugs, you're trafficking
firearms, you get caught.

21:46.146 --> 21:47.789
I'm sorry. There are consequences.

21:47.813 --> 21:50.664
His crew, whoever he was working with,

21:50.688 --> 21:52.914
they're gonna kill him when he's inside.

21:52.938 --> 21:55.205
Yeah, that might be
the definition of consequences.

21:55.229 --> 21:57.247
But does the punishment fit the crime?

21:57.271 --> 21:59.580
- Crimes past, present or future?
- So you think we should ignore it?

21:59.604 --> 22:01.580
- Ignore what?
- It's our job

22:01.604 --> 22:02.955
to represent our clients

22:02.979 --> 22:05.622
to the best of our abilities.
Suppressing evidence--

22:05.646 --> 22:07.705
Objection. "Suppressing" is questionable.

22:07.729 --> 22:10.664
One might even say inflammatory phrasing
in this particular instance, Counselor.

22:10.688 --> 22:12.664
Aren't you supposed to be
the Catholic one here?

22:12.688 --> 22:15.729
Oh, come on. All right, so, fine,
you want to go with guilt now?

22:20.063 --> 22:21.479
How about mercy?

22:22.729 --> 22:25.229
There's got to be something
about that in the Bible.

22:26.188 --> 22:27.521
Second chances,

22:28.063 --> 22:29.104
redemption?

22:30.771 --> 22:33.813
All I know is if he goes to jail, he dies.

22:34.854 --> 22:38.396
And all I know is that
might not be our problem.

22:38.979 --> 22:40.521
Unfortunately...

22:41.563 --> 22:42.604
it is now.

22:46.813 --> 22:47.813
This is Wesley.

22:48.146 --> 22:49.664
That's great to hear.

22:49.688 --> 22:51.646
Let me talk to him. I'll call you back.

22:53.063 --> 22:54.646
I take it he's available?

22:55.438 --> 22:57.354
He's here for a couple of weeks, just...

22:58.104 --> 22:59.289
moving through town.

22:59.313 --> 23:01.104
He's good. Very good.

23:01.979 --> 23:03.021
Maybe the best.

23:04.688 --> 23:05.688
Use him.

23:06.896 --> 23:08.646
We're a go.

23:12.479 --> 23:14.705
<i>His approval ratings
suggest otherwise.</i>

23:14.729 --> 23:16.039
<i>Good afternoon, Brian.</i>

23:16.063 --> 23:18.372
<i>Breaking news, just in to</i> New York One.

23:18.396 --> 23:21.664
<i>I am standing just outside
the entrance to Metro General Hospital.</i>

23:21.688 --> 23:24.080
<i>Here on Fifth Avenue, where we understand</i>

23:24.104 --> 23:26.497
<i>Vanessa Fisk is in critical condition.</i>

23:26.521 --> 23:28.330
Fucking BB, no way.

23:28.354 --> 23:30.414
<i>...in last night's
violent attack on...</i>

23:30.438 --> 23:31.497
- Mr. Blake.
- No way.

23:31.521 --> 23:32.955
- Can I get an update on Mrs. Fisk?
- No way. No.

23:32.979 --> 23:35.497
- Can you do me a favor and fuck off?
- And who the hell are you?

23:35.521 --> 23:37.521
I'm the one telling you
to fuck off. Keep up.

23:37.896 --> 23:39.396
Do I need to call the Task Force?

23:43.688 --> 23:45.021
They're horrible. Trust me.

23:50.271 --> 23:51.313
Thanks for that.

23:55.979 --> 23:57.039
Tough day.

23:57.063 --> 23:58.063
The worst.

23:59.188 --> 24:00.813
Buck, where were you last night?

24:01.604 --> 24:02.771
I had to run an errand.

24:03.688 --> 24:05.146
- How is he?
- Better.

24:05.896 --> 24:07.205
She's out of surgery.

24:07.229 --> 24:09.664
It's too soon to tell,
but it's not bad news so far.

24:09.688 --> 24:11.021
- Thank Christ.
- Mmm-hmm.

24:12.771 --> 24:14.479
You know, I could kill for a hot dog.

24:16.229 --> 24:17.438
Yeah, sure.

24:17.896 --> 24:18.896
Come on.

24:21.688 --> 24:22.688
<i>It's done.</i>

24:23.229 --> 24:24.330
Yes.

24:24.354 --> 24:25.354
Yes, indeed.

24:26.188 --> 24:27.479
The surgery went quite well.

24:28.854 --> 24:29.979
Tell me everything.

24:30.771 --> 24:33.997
Well, the procedure was long,
as you know, and quite involved.

24:34.021 --> 24:35.021
But...

24:35.438 --> 24:37.354
I'm optimistic in nature.

24:37.854 --> 24:38.979
And I remain hopeful.

24:40.396 --> 24:41.396
Hope?

24:44.729 --> 24:46.354
She's gonna be fine.

24:50.854 --> 24:52.580
<i>Please lean it against the wall.</i>

24:52.604 --> 24:54.271
I'll deal with it later.

24:58.854 --> 25:01.247
So, same spot, different piece?

25:01.271 --> 25:02.313
Mmm-hmm.

25:03.729 --> 25:05.563
I hope you know what you're doing.

25:54.146 --> 25:57.372
You know, there's hot dog carts
on every corner.

25:57.396 --> 25:59.247
Yeah,
I thought we might take a drive.

25:59.271 --> 26:00.414
Have a little chat.

26:00.438 --> 26:01.622
A chat?

26:01.646 --> 26:03.539
Buck, Fisk needs me.

26:03.563 --> 26:05.955
The man is aware we're going to Albany.

26:05.979 --> 26:07.979
Yo, Albany?

26:09.438 --> 26:11.396
Dude, you didn't say
anything about Albany.

26:13.688 --> 26:16.688
The other day in your office,
you were asking about my background.

26:17.063 --> 26:19.063
- Yeah, sure.
- Well, you were right.

26:19.688 --> 26:20.854
I was Regiment 22.

26:23.979 --> 26:27.479
When you were reading about my past,
did you see anything about Helmand?

26:28.813 --> 26:29.813
The mayonnaise?

26:31.354 --> 26:33.063
No, Daniel, not the mayonnaise.

26:33.646 --> 26:34.688
Afghanistan.

26:36.188 --> 26:40.205
My squadron, and I imagine many others,
were tasked with night raids,

26:40.229 --> 26:43.563
that no man of fighting age
would survive the night.

26:44.396 --> 26:47.039
But it was opium farmers, not insurgents.

26:47.063 --> 26:49.771
Apparently, Her Majesty
considered 14 fighting age.

26:52.604 --> 26:54.229
Jesus Christ, what did you do?

26:57.063 --> 26:58.188
What I was ordered to.

26:59.979 --> 27:00.979
That's my point.

27:02.854 --> 27:05.164
There are pivotal moments
in a man's life, Daniel,

27:05.188 --> 27:08.313
which define what kind of man he is,

27:08.813 --> 27:09.979
what he's really made of.

27:10.479 --> 27:13.021
Mr. Fisk changed my life
in one of those moments.

27:13.646 --> 27:15.104
I imagine you can relate, right?

27:16.313 --> 27:18.188
Staten Island to City Hall.

27:18.646 --> 27:20.104
Head of communications.

27:20.854 --> 27:22.438
That's quite a trajectory.

27:24.354 --> 27:25.813
That's impressive, Daniel.

27:27.646 --> 27:28.789
Appreciate that.

27:28.813 --> 27:30.813
My God, it has not been easy, has it?

27:31.438 --> 27:33.896
Muse, The <i>Northern Star</i> leak.

27:35.063 --> 27:38.771
And now it seems someone, God knows who,
has leaked the hospital to the press.

27:42.229 --> 27:44.313
What? You're not saying you think it's me,
are you?

27:45.771 --> 27:47.979
Buck, I didn't have
anything to do with that.

27:49.063 --> 27:50.521
Let's just take a left in here.

28:03.979 --> 28:05.354
Buck, am I in trouble?

28:08.063 --> 28:09.188
Be right back.

28:10.271 --> 28:11.789
Well, maybe I'll just come in with you.

28:11.813 --> 28:14.188
Get some beef jerky or help you out,
or whatever.

28:15.021 --> 28:17.396
That's kind of you, Daniel.
But I'll take care of it.

28:18.563 --> 28:19.646
Just sit tight, yeah?

28:53.604 --> 28:54.771
Mmm!

29:43.604 --> 29:44.938
Long time, pal.

29:45.938 --> 29:47.563
Looking good, Wes.

29:48.313 --> 29:50.771
Fucking hell.
You've come up in the world, haven't you?

29:51.104 --> 29:52.313
Living the dream.

29:53.229 --> 29:55.521
I understand you have
some sort of open assignment.

29:56.313 --> 29:57.813
We're looking to you for...

29:58.354 --> 29:59.521
creativity.

30:05.104 --> 30:07.354
Well, you've come to
the right place, then, haven't you?

30:09.188 --> 30:11.688
Sign here.

30:17.604 --> 30:18.771
Do you need anything?

30:21.479 --> 30:22.729
What are you gonna do now?

30:24.646 --> 30:25.979
What am I gonna do?

30:26.854 --> 30:29.396
I don't know.
Wait for 'em to come find me.

30:33.396 --> 30:35.271
All right. Good to see you, Fembot.

30:41.938 --> 30:44.080
You recognize this place,
you piece of shit?

30:44.104 --> 30:45.687
Fuck.

30:52.688 --> 30:55.063
We should be safe here for now.

30:55.271 --> 30:58.146
Safe?

30:58.979 --> 31:00.479
What does that even mean?

31:02.021 --> 31:03.979
You know what happens if she dies?

31:04.479 --> 31:06.938
Fisk turns the city upside-down
and shakes it

31:07.771 --> 31:09.104
until he finds us...

31:09.813 --> 31:10.997
and kills us.

31:11.021 --> 31:12.330
Uh, me.

31:12.354 --> 31:13.747
- Kills me.
- Us.

31:13.771 --> 31:14.771
I was there.

31:15.521 --> 31:17.396
That is more than enough for Fisk.

31:28.521 --> 31:29.563
It's open.

31:34.396 --> 31:36.188
What the fuck you doing here, Foggy?

31:37.896 --> 31:39.771
<i>I know someone who can help.</i>

31:40.354 --> 31:41.997
- A nurse.
- Nurses,

31:42.021 --> 31:43.604
doctors...

31:44.438 --> 31:45.604
lawyers.

31:46.396 --> 31:48.896
Vigilantes, assassins.

31:49.813 --> 31:52.063
Killing people, saving people.

31:54.688 --> 31:56.396
Act like it makes a difference.

31:58.104 --> 31:59.729
Like it matters at all.

32:01.479 --> 32:02.813
<i>I wanted to give you this.</i>

32:06.063 --> 32:07.063
The hell is this?

32:07.646 --> 32:10.688
I was hoping you'd take that,
and, I don't know...

32:12.146 --> 32:13.205
get out of here.

32:13.229 --> 32:14.896
I don't even know where, but...

32:15.438 --> 32:16.955
Wait, wait, wait. So you--

32:16.979 --> 32:18.688
- You gonna give me money?
- No.

32:19.563 --> 32:21.729
Ray, I already gave it to you.

32:22.396 --> 32:25.396
What I want is for you
to start over with it.

32:25.896 --> 32:27.604
You got a second chance here.

32:28.063 --> 32:30.354
It's not about them. It's about you.

32:32.271 --> 32:33.271
About me.

32:35.396 --> 32:36.521
Just people...

32:39.354 --> 32:40.354
and, brother...

32:41.896 --> 32:44.395
we are who we are.

32:47.938 --> 32:49.229
<i>You know those nights...</i>

32:50.063 --> 32:51.063
we used to, uh...

32:52.438 --> 32:54.771
crash in the living room. Um...

32:56.438 --> 32:57.747
Well, you and Connor

32:57.771 --> 33:00.705
with the, uh, sleeping bags and...

33:00.729 --> 33:03.229
...uh, the flashlights, you know?

33:05.813 --> 33:08.271
I never really, uh,
had a friend like that.

33:09.938 --> 33:10.938
I know.

33:14.313 --> 33:15.979
<i>We're all doing the same thing here.</i>

33:17.771 --> 33:20.646
Acting something out,
scratching some kinda itch.

33:22.021 --> 33:23.313
But the worst part...

33:25.063 --> 33:26.854
is when you think you got it beat.

33:27.979 --> 33:29.063
You think...

33:30.229 --> 33:31.563
"I outran it."

33:34.521 --> 33:36.479
Then you turn the corner, bam...

33:38.771 --> 33:39.854
there it is...

33:41.604 --> 33:43.313
staring you right in the face.

33:45.813 --> 33:47.396
Only it's worse this time.

33:50.396 --> 33:51.438
And, you know...

33:54.688 --> 33:56.479
it was always gonna be there.

33:57.354 --> 33:58.813
<i>Hey, do me a favor, will you?</i>

33:59.438 --> 34:01.396
Tell my brother to stay
right where he's at.

34:02.854 --> 34:05.563
All right? You tell him
I told you to tell him that,

34:06.104 --> 34:08.146
that he ain't got nothing
back here for him.

34:11.104 --> 34:12.188
He's got you.

34:19.271 --> 34:21.271
Come on, Foggy. You gotta go, man.
Get out of here.

34:25.688 --> 34:27.188
<i>There's no escaping it.</i>

34:33.896 --> 34:35.438
I'm sorry to interrupt.

34:35.813 --> 34:38.188
This church will always provide shelter

34:38.854 --> 34:40.146
to both of you, but...

34:41.646 --> 34:43.438
I think they know you're here.

34:50.021 --> 34:51.455
Good evening, officers.
How can I help you?

34:51.479 --> 34:52.747
Hello, Father.

34:52.771 --> 34:55.664
You haven't by chance seen a couple of
vigilantes this fine evening, have you?

34:55.688 --> 34:59.021
I've been in prayers all afternoon,
Officer. I... I don't believe I have.

35:07.938 --> 35:10.229
Listen, we gotta come check the place out.
Mayor's orders.

35:12.479 --> 35:13.479
Just...

35:14.521 --> 35:15.604
go.

35:16.771 --> 35:18.063
Don't be an idiot.

35:18.729 --> 35:19.854
Leave me.

35:20.271 --> 35:23.247
Oh, I'm sorry, but weapons are not
permitted in the house of God.

35:23.271 --> 35:24.646
The rules have changed.

35:25.521 --> 35:27.271
Come on in, boys. Sweep it!

35:28.604 --> 35:29.938
<i>I killed your friend...</i>

35:30.313 --> 35:31.313
Foggy.

35:31.771 --> 35:33.146
I didn't think twice.

35:33.646 --> 35:35.270
That's who I am.

35:40.729 --> 35:42.146
Just let me die.

35:44.313 --> 35:45.313
I don't...

35:48.021 --> 35:49.497
Look, I can't save us both.

35:49.521 --> 35:50.938
I'm sorry. I tried.

35:56.396 --> 35:58.146
Let's go! Let's go!

35:59.438 --> 36:02.021
Sir! Let's go. Move!

36:04.354 --> 36:05.979
<i>Imagine my surprise...</i>

36:07.188 --> 36:10.080
when I came back to the office
and found the empty book.

36:10.104 --> 36:11.247
How did you know?

36:11.271 --> 36:13.997
Spend enough time in the same tiny office
with the same person,

36:14.021 --> 36:15.581
you tend to know what they're thinking.

36:22.146 --> 36:23.146
I'm sorry.

36:25.313 --> 36:26.562
I'll pay it back.

36:30.104 --> 36:32.063
Foggy the Fembot.

36:32.979 --> 36:35.497
And there I was thinking
the Murdock and Nelson fund

36:35.521 --> 36:37.354
was supposed to be about the future.

36:38.396 --> 36:39.896
It is, Matt.

36:41.813 --> 36:43.188
<i>But not just ours.</i>

36:47.979 --> 36:48.979
<i>So, where to now?</i>

36:50.063 --> 36:51.830
- Josie's.
- Obviously.

36:51.854 --> 36:52.979
What are we celebrating?

36:55.438 --> 36:56.563
Mercy.

37:15.229 --> 37:16.229
Fuck.

37:18.813 --> 37:19.979
Where'd he go?

37:38.938 --> 37:40.688
You really don't have to do this, man.

37:43.688 --> 37:45.747
I don't even know what I did.
But whatever it was,

37:45.771 --> 37:48.021
it was probably stupid,
and I probably deserve it.

37:49.104 --> 37:50.729
But I could just walk away, man.

37:51.521 --> 37:53.330
I could just disa-fucking-ppear,

37:53.354 --> 37:56.646
and you wouldn't hear anything from me.
Not a peep, not a tweet. Nothing.

37:58.604 --> 38:01.563
Man, I'd be like-- I'd be like Casper.
I mean, I'd be like a ghost.

38:07.979 --> 38:09.479
<i>Look, I didn't fucking leak it.</i>

38:10.271 --> 38:11.271
It wasn't me.

38:14.604 --> 38:15.604
I promise.

38:17.896 --> 38:19.354
Get out of the car, Daniel.

38:30.521 --> 38:31.521
Delivery.

38:49.604 --> 38:50.854
I like you, Daniel.

38:52.313 --> 38:53.438
I really do.

38:54.521 --> 38:56.646
But we work for a man
who can change your life.

38:58.396 --> 38:59.646
<i>Has changed your life.</i>

39:01.146 --> 39:02.646
<i>And all he asks in return...</i>

39:03.729 --> 39:04.729
<i>is loyalty.</i>

39:06.063 --> 39:07.146
<i>Unbridled,</i>

39:07.854 --> 39:09.146
<i>unquestioned...</i>

39:10.021 --> 39:11.688
- loyalty.
- Well, I've been loyal.

39:12.396 --> 39:13.938
I've stayed loyal, Buck.

39:15.646 --> 39:16.854
I'll do anything.

39:18.104 --> 39:20.997
I've said it before.
I'll do whatever it takes.

39:21.021 --> 39:22.104
Please.

39:23.979 --> 39:25.021
Make a choice.

39:32.313 --> 39:33.313
Saw...

39:33.979 --> 39:35.354
or shovel.

39:56.729 --> 39:57.896
You know, I was thinking.

39:59.146 --> 40:00.830
Maybe, uh,

40:00.854 --> 40:02.729
instead of Murdock and Nelson,

40:03.188 --> 40:05.813
maybe it's Nelson and Murdock.

40:06.979 --> 40:08.372
- I like that.
- Yeah?

40:08.396 --> 40:09.455
I bumped you up.

40:09.479 --> 40:11.080
- I love that.
- You're goin' up in the world, buddy.

40:11.104 --> 40:12.830
I am going up in the world.

40:12.854 --> 40:15.539
And I think the next 50 rounds are on you.

40:15.563 --> 40:17.580
I don't know about 50.
Fifty sounds a little...

40:17.604 --> 40:19.812
- Forty-nine. Sold.
- Forty-seven.

40:42.229 --> 40:43.728
Little help?

41:06.813 --> 41:08.146
Vanessa.

41:08.646 --> 41:09.747
You're here.

41:09.771 --> 41:11.354
Yes, I'm here.

41:12.729 --> 41:14.354
I'm right here.

41:15.354 --> 41:16.979
It's so good to see you.

41:18.104 --> 41:20.354
Why are you acting so strange?

41:21.021 --> 41:22.021
Well, I... I...

41:22.479 --> 41:23.604
I didn't think... I...

41:24.604 --> 41:25.688
I didn't think that...

41:26.313 --> 41:28.396
You didn't think what?

41:32.813 --> 41:33.813
I just...

41:34.188 --> 41:35.438
I wasn't...

41:39.271 --> 41:41.313
I wasn't sure that I would see you again.

41:43.563 --> 41:45.622
That's absurd. I'm right here.

41:45.646 --> 41:47.354
Yes, of course. Of course you are.

41:47.646 --> 41:49.354
Yes, you are right here. Of course.

41:54.188 --> 41:56.330
What can I do? Can I do something for you?

41:56.354 --> 41:58.789
Are you thirsty?
Can I get you something to drink?

41:58.813 --> 42:00.664
Like water, or...

42:00.688 --> 42:03.205
Or are you hungry?
I can get you something to eat.

42:03.229 --> 42:05.747
Anything. I--
I could get anything you want.

42:05.771 --> 42:06.830
Yes.

42:06.854 --> 42:09.271
I'd like a pineapple juice.

42:10.104 --> 42:11.229
With ice.

42:13.313 --> 42:14.896
You don't like pineapple.

42:15.396 --> 42:16.396
I don't?

42:16.854 --> 42:18.039
No. Your-- Your lips.

42:18.063 --> 42:20.229
It-- It makes them tingle, I believe.

42:25.188 --> 42:26.705
Let's try anyway.

42:26.729 --> 42:27.938
- Mmm-hmm.
- Shall we?

42:28.354 --> 42:29.414
Yeah. Nurse?

42:29.438 --> 42:30.438
Nurse!

42:30.563 --> 42:31.622
Is everything okay?

42:31.646 --> 42:33.789
No. I mean, she's awake.

42:33.813 --> 42:36.580
Wait. She wants a pineapple juice.

42:36.604 --> 42:37.914
Sir, I need to--

42:37.938 --> 42:38.938
No!

42:39.854 --> 42:42.563
Pineapple juice in a glass, with ice.

42:43.729 --> 42:46.039
- Wilson.
- Yes?

42:46.063 --> 42:48.122
Why did you scare the poor girl? She--

42:48.146 --> 42:49.205
No.

42:49.229 --> 42:52.188
- You practically made her cry.
- No, I, I just... Um...

42:52.896 --> 42:55.313
I'm just overwhelmed, my love, that's all.

42:57.021 --> 42:58.164
Please.

42:58.188 --> 42:59.688
I've never seen you like this.

43:00.646 --> 43:01.979
I just thought that...

43:04.354 --> 43:06.747
I'm just glad you're with me here again.

43:06.771 --> 43:07.771
That's all.

43:08.729 --> 43:09.789
But...

43:09.813 --> 43:11.563
why did you think I'd gone?

43:12.021 --> 43:13.021
I don't know.

43:14.354 --> 43:15.354
I, uh...

43:17.104 --> 43:18.938
I just missed you so much.

43:19.396 --> 43:21.455
That's all. I just missed you so much.

43:21.479 --> 43:22.914
I missed you, too.

43:22.938 --> 43:25.938
- Yeah?
- I'm so glad to be here with you.

43:30.063 --> 43:31.063
Yes, baby.

43:43.896 --> 43:46.063
Is there something else you need, my dear?

43:46.938 --> 43:47.938
No.

43:49.438 --> 43:50.771
That was divine.

43:51.438 --> 43:52.438
Good.

43:55.688 --> 43:56.688
Wilson.

43:57.271 --> 43:58.580
Yes, my love.

43:58.604 --> 44:00.188
Will you tell me a story?

44:02.271 --> 44:03.396
A story?

44:05.063 --> 44:06.372
Yes.

44:06.396 --> 44:08.604
A story, please.

44:10.063 --> 44:12.313
What kind of story
would you like me to tell?

44:13.313 --> 44:15.438
Tell me the story of how we met.

44:17.729 --> 44:19.229
Oh.

44:26.271 --> 44:28.979
I've arranged for a more private
showing, but...

44:29.854 --> 44:30.854
this is it.

44:31.271 --> 44:32.438
This is the gallery.

44:36.188 --> 44:39.622
<i>Somehow, I must have known
that you would walk</i>

44:39.646 --> 44:42.021
<i>through those doors and change everything.</i>

44:43.354 --> 44:45.146
Lucky then, I guess, that day.

44:45.771 --> 44:47.563
Mmm, no.

44:48.188 --> 44:49.188
Not luck.

44:50.646 --> 44:51.771
Not luck at all.

44:53.563 --> 44:55.872
It was the grand design.

44:55.896 --> 44:57.771
Mmm.

44:59.104 --> 45:01.312
Though you did vastly overpay.

45:05.313 --> 45:06.539
Did I?

45:06.563 --> 45:09.122
Three times the listing price.

45:09.146 --> 45:10.664
I would have paid anything.

45:10.688 --> 45:12.813
That day was the...

45:13.521 --> 45:15.146
The deal of the century.

45:16.021 --> 45:17.021
Wilson.

45:19.604 --> 45:20.854
Yes, my love?

45:23.146 --> 45:24.854
Will you tell me a story?

45:25.188 --> 45:26.188
Please?

45:27.896 --> 45:29.563
Will you tell me a story?

45:31.354 --> 45:33.396
Can you tell me the story...

45:34.438 --> 45:35.646
of how...

45:36.854 --> 45:37.938
we...

45:44.104 --> 45:45.104
Yes.

45:47.854 --> 45:50.330
Vanessa.

45:50.354 --> 45:52.164
Vanessa.

45:52.188 --> 45:53.705
Vanessa!

45:53.729 --> 45:54.955
Vanessa!

45:54.979 --> 45:56.437
I need some help now!

46:55.688 --> 46:57.021
Well, hello there.
